      "content": "small acts don't change anything. i go through the motions like a robot, but i'm not really here. i feel like i'm already dead, just walking around in a shell. it feels so dishonest to keep pretending that life is still happening when the only person who actually made it feel real is gone. it's just exhausting to keep fighting for a life that doesn't even feel like mine anymore.",
